            {
                "s2_paper_id": "2d7944f84a9410dba529e17bc38eecddecda4ce5",
                "title": "Contact structures, sutured Floer homology and TQFT",
                "year": 2008,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 82,
                "reference_count": 27,
                "abstract": "We describe the natural gluing map on sutured Floer homology which is induced by the inclusion of one sutured manifold (M',\\Gamma') into a larger sutured manifold (M,\\Gamma), together with a contact structure on M-M'. As an application of this gluing map, we produce a (1+1)-dimensional TQFT by dimensional reduction and study its properties.",
